<br>
There's 5 circles of spells to get notes from.<br>
<br>
There's 5 levels past 60<br>
<br>
So it could very well be that it's Note A + class's spell used in that note of level 39 == level 61 spell for that class, and so on for each one.<br>
<br>
Paralyzing earth wouldn't be used I do not think, it's more a general spell that isn't specific to a class. The enchanter spell is most likely allure.<br>
<br>
I believe the level 39 and 49 spells will be the researched spells for that level. Just aren't any dropped spells for those levels, well, not enough to fit the formulae. The level 44, 50, and 52 spells used are all drops from the expansions, which is basiclly what replaced research. Most of the level 39 and 49 spells are old world spells, so it stands to reason that these are comparable to dropped spells of the expansions.<br>
<br>
Considering these are for level 61+ spells, I do not believe it would use any storebought spells. These are alternatives to collectiing parchments from the planes, which while simpler, is harder to accomplish.<br>
<br>
How many possible combinations of notes would there be if you had 5 notes that were arranged in a sequences of 4 ?<br>
<br>
I'm thinking might need to arrange differant &quot;compositions&quot; with the notes in the research box to make differant spells. Like A+C+E+B would make one spell while A+B+C+D would make something else.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
