<br>
Has anyone tried putting the item you get back from a note into our proper research container and seeing if it combines ?<br>
<br>
Follow my logic here:<br>
<br>
- The quest is open to all classes with the research skill (int casters). Well anyone could get the box, but without research skill, they couldn't go anywhere with it.<br>
<br>
- So I'd dismiss the idea that any combines will relate specificlly to magicians<br>
<br>
- The box we're given is an extractor. I don't think we're supposed to use it to do anything but extract whatever it is a particular sage is seeking.<br>
<br>
- We assemble spells up to level 49 from various materials in our respective classes tomes. Stands to reason that we may in fact use our standard tome to use the pieces we get back in some way to make the new spells.<br>
<br>
The above of course is entirely speculation. From working on this lately, I am starting to wonder if some portions might be broken, I have yet to find a single item with an effect that can be disassembled in the box, but granted I haven't had that large of a sample to test with.<br>
<br>
In the end we may need a combination of items acquired from each of the sages to construct a spell. Problem with that theory is that not all the research tomes have that many slots, some only can hold 2 items. When I get back on tommorow I'll see if the amulet can be combined in an elemental binder to produce anything. Guessing it won't, but it's worth a shot.<br>
<br>
Also starting to wonder if in fact these quests will actually produce spells as the end result. This may just be introducing us to a way to construct magic items using our research skill.<br>
<br>
Kinelaria<br>
Taeru<br>
Lana<br>
<br>
